We have distributed "protected" software and documents on CD-ROM
using encryption/verification based on the hardware ethernet rom
address of the host machine or the checksum of the volume home
block or bad track list of the hard disk.

This local identifier allows issuing a unique permission code
to the user. For databases, the data must remain encrypted and
be accessed through a controlled software program.

Of course each product can be protected individually. We even use 
a "vendor code" to allow each vendor to generate his own passwords.

